edu.wit.dcsn.comp2000.bag.adt

Class LinkedBag<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.wit.dcsn.comp2000.bag.adt.LinkedBag<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The class of items the LinkedBag will hold.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    BagInterface<T>

    public final class LinkedBag<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements BagInterface<T>
    A class of bags whose entries are stored in a chain of linked nodes. The bag is never full.
    Version:
    4.1, 4.2.0 2016-01-10 Reformat and revise, 4.3.0 2019-05-12 Add 'cloning' constructor, difference(), intersection(), union(), 4.4.0 2019-05-24 standardize on resultBag for returned construct variable name for difference(), intersection(), union(), 4.5.0 2020-01-28
    • add constructor taking array of entries
    • move Node to a separate class
    , 4.6.0 2020-05-16 add check for null argument to difference(), 4.7.0 2020-08-08 track changes to BagInterface - now extend EnhancedBagInterface instead, 4.8.0 2020-09-13
    • track changes to BagInterface.java - switch back to it
    • copy all Javadoc comments from BagInterface.java to here instead of referencing them
    Author:
    Frank M. Carrano, Timothy M. Henry, David M Rosenberg

      • LinkedBag

        public LinkedBag(BagInterface<T> sourceBag)
        Initialize a new LinkedBag and populate it with the contents of sourceBag
        Parameters:
        sourceBag - another bag containing zero or more entries to copy to the newly instantiated LinkedBag

        Note: sourceBag is an instance of any class that implements BagInterface - it doesn't have to be another LinkedBag

        Note: the contents of sourceBag are unchanged.
